Oduduwa College, Ile Ife, Old Students Association (1974-79 set) has renovated the school’s administrative building as part of activi­ties to mark the 40th anni­versary of the set. The dedication and formal hand over of the renovated Oba Adesoji Aderemi Administrative Building built in 1932, to the school manage­ment would take place on Saturday, November 9, during the 40th annu­al re-union celebrations of the old students in the school compound. Other highlights of the event billed for 12 noon at the school’s hall include presentation of awards to the best JSS 2 and SSS 2 students in the 2018/2019 promo­tional examinations and distribution of free ex­ercise books to current students of the school.